news.title: Sales of luxury home surge 37.8% in first nine months of 2024: Report
news.para: Total sales of luxury homes during the first nine months of this year stood at 12,625 compared to 9,160 units during the same period last year.

news.title: Institutional investment in real estate up 31% to $4.61 billion in Jan-Sept 2024: Report
news.para: Real estate consultant Vestian on Monday released its report on 'Investment in Indian Real Estate', observing that funds' inflow from institutional investors in the first nine months of 2024 has already surpassed the total for 2023.

news.title: UltraTech Cement's net profit dips 35.55% in Q2 FY25
news.para: UltraTech Cement's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 15,855.46 crore in Q2 FY25, a dip of two per cent from Rs 16,179.26 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: MPMRCL reviews Bhopal metro corridor construction from AIIMS to DRM Office
news.para: The metro priority corridor was scheduled to be completed by May 2024. This announcement was made during a trial run that took place in Sept 2023.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP issues notice to 11 markets to remove encroachments
news.para: Notice issued to DLF 1 shopping mall, Galleria market in DLF 4, and Vyapar Kendra in Sushant Lok 1, to remove encroachments within a week. Demolitions will be carried out and penalties imposed if the markets fail to comply.

news.title: Telangana government to build 20 lakh Indiramma houses in next four years
news.para: 3,500 to 4,000 Indiramma housing units will be sanctioned in the first phase in each of the 119 assembly constituencies in the state by Oct-end

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government approves two master plans for Noida and YEIDA
news.para: The Noida master plan 2041 focuses primarily on the expansion of the Dadri-Noida-Ghaziabad Investment Region (DNGIR), commonly referred to as New Noida. The project will involve acquiring land from 80 villages across Gautam Budh Nagar and Bulandshahr districts.

news.title: Conciliation forums resolved 1,749 or 32% homebuyers’ complaints: Maharashtra RERA
news.para: With this, of the 5,958 complaints filed with MahaRERA, around 32% have been resolved through these 52 Conciliation Forums in the state, often leading to mutually agreed-upon settlements, MahaRERA said.

news.title: Asking prices for homes in UK rise 0.3% in October 2024: Rightmove
news.para: Asking prices rose by just 0.3% in October, well below their average for a 1.3% monthly increase for the month, property website Rightmove said.

news.title: Lucknow development body offers discount on flats
news.para: Under this initiative, homebuyers can receive direct discount ranging from Rs 1 lakh to Rs 2.5 lakh on flats.

news.title: Suraj Estate Developers raises Rs 343 crore
news.para: The funds will be utilized by Suraj Estate Developers for land acquisitions, working capital, general corporate purposes, and issue related expenses.

news.title: Prestige Estates to invest Rs 7,000 crore to develop township in Ghaziabad
news.para: Prestige Estates has also forayed into Delhi-NCR housing market by acquiring three land parcels in Delhi, Noida and Siddharth Vihar, Ghaziabad.

news.title: Notice issued to 251 construction sites in Noida for not registering on dust audit portal
news.para: The notice, dated Oct 20, seeks environmental compensation totalling more than Rs 3.39 crore.

news.title: Noida authority seals three unsold shops in Prateek Laurel society
news.para: As of Dec 31, 2023, the developer owed the Authority a total of Rs 50.49 crore. Despite repeated notices, Prateek Realtors deposited only Rs 1.5 crore out of the required Rs 12.62 crore, which is 25% of the total dues.

news.title: Haryana DTCP to hold hearing for architects issuing occupation certificates
news.para: After these hearings, it will be determined whether their registrations will remain cancelled or if they will be allowed to continue by paying the penalty.

news.title: FPCE urges government for real estate guidelines under consumer protection act
news.para: The association pointed out that the consumer forums constituted under Consumer Protection Act 2019 comprises about 10 per cent of their complaints from the consumers of real estate sector.

news.title: MREAT directs Cidco to register with MahaRERA as promoter for disposal of plots
news.para: ​​It further directed Cidco to register as a promoter (TD) before MahaRERA for its future town development projects initiated under its scheme akin to the scheme in 2017-18, before advertising, selling, or marketing its planned land plots.

news.title: Bombay HC registers new petition over illegal constructions in Goa
news.para: Advocate general Devidas Pangam told reporters that the high court is concerned about all illegal constructions by the side of roads, in coastal regulation zones (CRZ), and within the jurisdictions of panchayats and municipalities.

news.title: About 110 government buildings in Ghaziabad yet to pay nearly Rs 300 crore municipal taxes
news.para: GMC's chief tax assessment officer Sanjeev Singh said a central govt rule mandates municipalities across the country to levy service charges for services, like roads, water, drainage networks and streetlights, on all central and state govt buildings and installations.

news.title: Will support genuine builders: Telangana CM
news.para: Sources told TOI that realtors and developers recently expressed significant concerns to ministers about the negative impact on the real estate sector stemming from the feared demolitions related to the HYDRA initiative.
